   <body>
      <context/>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Route the input cables through the top gland plate and
connect to the input busbars (L1, L2, L3, N) and to the ground busbar
in the top entry cabinet.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the Top Entry Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/50kva_ups_and_top_entry_cabinet_1P_connect-cables_120mm_0000166012.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Route the output cables through the top gland plate and
connect to the output busbars (L1, L2, L3, N) and to the ground busbar
in the top entry cabinet.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Only in systems with remote battery cabinet(s):
Route the battery cables from the remote battery cabinet(s) through
the top gland plate and connect to the battery busbars (+, –)
and the ground busbar in the top entry cabinet.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Route the preinstalled cables from the top entry cabinet
through the transformer cabinet (if present) and into the UPS cabinet
as shown.</p>
            <stepxmp>
